10	1	Speak Now (Taylor's Version)	2023-07-07	https://e-cdns-images.dzcdn.net/images/cover/c1613c3579a594bce2ebc77bccfaa4e7/1000x1000-000000-80-0-0.jpg	album	Speak Now (Taylor's Version) is the third re-recorded album by Taylor Swift, released on July 7, 2023, via Republic Records. It is a re-recording of Swift's third studio album, Speak Now. The re-recording is a part of Swift's counteraction to her 2019 masters dispute. The album was announced on May 5, 2023, at the first Nashville show of her ongoing concert tour, the Eras Tour.\n\nThe 22-track Speak Now (Taylor's Version) was solely written by Swift. It includes re-recorded versions of 16 songs from the deluxe edition of Speak Now and six previously unreleased "From the Vault" songs. Swift and Christopher Rowe produced the album, with new inputs from Aaron Dessner and Jack Antonoff. American rock acts Fall Out Boy and Hayley Williams of Paramore contributed guest vocals.	f
