469	20	Stick Season (We'll All Be Here Forever)	2023-06-09	https://e-cdns-images.dzcdn.net/images/cover/1cf9edd5673e4f9a070054fbd6166134/1000x1000-000000-80-0-0.jpg	album	Stick Season (We'll All Be Here Forever) is the expanded version of Noah Kahan's third studio album, and was released on June 9, 2023, with seven additional tracks, including an extended version of "The View Between Villages".\n\nOn November 7, 2022 Noah first shared the idea of a deluxe version of his album Stick Season, a mere three weeks after its release. Describing the album as having “winter vibes”. On April 25, 2023 he confirmed that the recording of the Deluxe version was done, along with a presave link. The exact release date and tracklist of the album are still to be announced.\n\nOn May 2, 2023 Noah shared a TikTok in which he describes the process of making the Deluxe edition, opening up about the anxiety and fear of failure that having to follow up his biggest success caused him. He writes “I was completely lost in how to continue telling this story”.\n\nKahan decided to go back to the place that inspired him to make Stick Season in the first place: his home town. However, when he got there he discovered that it did not feel the same -he felt like a tourist. His home now served as a reminder of his self-described “impending failure”, making him feel even worse than he already did.\n\nNot being able to continue with this negativity, Noah describes letting go of his self-imposed pressure and anxiety, deciding instead to make this very letting go the theme of the deluxe album. He describes it best himself, when he talks about the Deluxe in comparison to the original Stick Season album:\n\n“Stick Season is a record that at times is full of bitterness and resentment towards those who left a place that the narrator could not. What if the Deluxe is about letting go of that resentment, and finding peace in sticking around?”	f
