794	33	UTOPIA	2023-07-28	https://e-cdns-images.dzcdn.net/images/cover/6c91e64b7157f1332a4f6b0de9e4c714/1000x1000-000000-80-0-0.jpg	album	UTOPIA is the fourth full-length studio album from the Houston, Texas native, Travis Scott. It is the follow-up to his 2018 third, highly-acclaimed studio album, ASTROWORLD.\n\nThe album was released to a flurry of various receptions. Many noted the obvious Kanye influences on the album, with a general consensus calling it “Travis Scott’s Yeezus.” Not only does he channel the broken down production on “MODERN JAM” and breathy flow on “CIRCUS MAXIMUS,” but three of the tracks were directly repurposed from the original demo of Donda. However, a similar affinity for guttural sound makes sense, as Travis was a vital collaborator in the production of Ye’s controversial sixth album. Yet, even the way he involved a slew of different A-listers and up-and-coming artists within his production evokes Ye’s own collaborative storms.\n\nSome found the album to be a generic amalgam of spectacle; others enjoyed the more experimental direction that Travis was taking.\n\nThe album was first teased through an Instagram post on July 8, 2020, with a simple caption which displayed “Utopia.” On August 3, 2020, during the second anniversary of Travis' previous album, ASTROWORLD, he would post a note thanking his fans for the support of his previous album on a tweet.\n\nIn June 2021, Scott described to WWD the sound of Utopia, stating that the album would have a psychedelic rock sound.\n\nIt was reported on August 2, 2021, that Travis Scott signed a production deal with the film company A24, with Travis posting on Instagram the first draft of the script, which revealed that UTOPIA would also have a film adaptation.\n\nDespite the album being rumored to be released in late 2021, it had been put on hold following the tragic Astroworld Festival crowd crush where 8-11 people ended up dying on the night of the festival.\n\nIn May 2023, Scott revealed that the album was in the mastering stages. The album was announced alongside his Great Pyramids Of Giza show for July 28, 2023, on July 10 through Travis' Twitter.\n\nNot long after “K-POP”’s release, on July 22, 2023, Travis confirmed the release of UTOPIA to be paired with the release of his movie Circus Maximus, hitting theaters on July 28, 2023, during his Rolling Loud Miami set at the GoPuff stage.\n\nTwo hours before the album was released, he revealed the tracklist without listing the features, similar to his previous two studio albums. However, days following the album’s release, the features were credited.	f
